 work. However, I notice an issue with getConstructor failing for the array. I need to ensure I have the success message covered at line 108, because after that success, the getConstructor failure might get caught.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_1PrkYC8zQ3qaUlQWGPUtI6cR|fc_0d3fee22a0f9aab50169f503b7227c8191958c1bd83209b77c", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "jshell --execution local <<'EOF'\ntry { System.out.println(ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader().loadClass(\"[I\")); } catch (Throwable t) { System.out.println(t); }\ntry { System.out.println(Class.forName(\"[I\")); } catch (Throwable t) { System.out.println(t); }\n/exit\nEOF", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 13795, "output": 2530, "cacheRead": 6144, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22469, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777664915372, "responseId": "resp_0d3fee22a0f9aab50169f5039442688191994a1aa7a712ac4e"}}
