[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering class loading in Java**\n\nI'm thinking about defining a custom message class in my test sources. For fallback success, it seems the POP3Store's classloader may struggle to load it, but using Class.forName should work. Wait, I remember that in modern Java, Class.forName(String) uses the caller's defining loader instead of the system. So, is Class.forName(className) effectively using the current class loader? The Javadoc indicates it uses the defining loader of the current class. That's interesting!\n\n**Evaluating class loading methods**\n\nI’m looking into how Class.forName(\"[Ljava.lang.String;\") works and whether ClassLoader.loadClass(\"[Ljava.lang.String;\") does too. I suspect that ClassLoader.loadClass can load an array class, so that might work. However, I notice an issue with getConstructor failing for the array. I need to ensure I have the success message covered at line 108, because after that success, the getConstructor failure might get caught.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d3fee22a0f9aab50169f50395190c81919db126e86b1fbfb7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9QO3R0XLmzM36zJWuGDb8UmdzRs7qfYjoZalseAi80zfIr6EngnJLGdU_bw9Lx9fvc_KiXHwqSY3ccKaAQ80t7gWPoBWdq1Lb9vS1Q9qefN58czgHFf9tqwQVw2XyzttphChL4t0SMhSReO-5z81jZu5H7JutQ-f7wCWqQyeOzdXRwQCT2aQfT5bCQksU_beJk7i7ukX40CVGvfLrH7sZ_4gTHrPuKji3Y8K95KpoRpteuVrujpKUM_JS6lgXvbdbOe3UVXkvdT40ynNwOdLbGp5xWM_q5sD1POleEZhbs5TEZwh4cPD3Oo18glk2-PWUci6W4kCjfSFsCNrrEzn7qtoOPiIUC7o6JDx_tG0Oj7bUMY-gbsq5gBkS3BSjM8wYEutsK8Yhlgf3Drlm-uouAn9jQ-i1k5rjG0Nhko7hIcaNXvTEi8tklgZ-QiFrv82JyfC_HVlsUs74o7oqm4lyJB5-5O_zo6ujrv4RgjurrmLLbr8dgCluiNA6W-4qCrArEoKUB8orcqoi_z095Noez0rJn5aFpZy3nknZO0ttrgjCUiL9mrc59eDDF-iGYuyWPNJWOCdHO0pmlVNlHfVntV_Riqu_60Mr0-v2YmvwUzbQhD5TayAT3QR0aRo9oR6IMejM5Suko0SgiVj-S7Kr2LGvp7blvijAweLcfsK1_lRYIzCrbN-sEc_vTgPqki43XHSrPtb0OUAIImvgSCz9A3Xiaj8mumG3yHFhNkUjwdTJqxFjt9yNYxCic